main event: Two elliptical shaped objects with a bright red color were observed off the north coast of Labrador. The objects were approximately 75 to 100 feet in diameter and traveled at tremendous speeds, estimated between 1,500 to 2,000 miles per hour. The objects were observed for approximately 2 to 3 minutes.
interesting points: The objects were observed from two different positions, suggesting there was definitely something in the area.
A ship called the 'Ikanook' was sent to search the area but failed to find anything.
The objects were described as cylinder-like, larger than an airplane, and had five portholes along the side.
The objects approached the surface of the ocean at an angle, hit, and disappeared underneath about fifteen miles away.
No air traffic was reported in the area at the time of the sighting.
sighted object: two elliptical shaped, bright red objects
